This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it discusses the architecture of deep neural networks and their inspiration from biological neuronal networks. Additionally, the paper also discusses the interplay between inter-neuronal network topology and cognition, which is a key area of research in neural computing. 

The paper also discusses the classification accuracy obtained by the Deep Connectomics Networks (DCNs), which suggests that it could belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

Furthermore, the paper discusses the architecture of DCNs inspired by the biological neuronal networks of C. Elegans and the mouse visual cortex, which suggests that it could belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision). 

The paper also discusses the topological aspects of deep neural networks, which suggests that it could belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). 

Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of DCNs in cognitive computing, which suggests that it could belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
